cards.title: This is where new cards are created by default
cards.description:
This card has been created in LeanKit's Defaiult Drop Lane. This lane has a special icon, telling users that this is where new cards go by default. 

Cards moved from other LeanKit boards will appear here, as well as cards created via email. 

Go ahead and try creating a card via email now! Just hover over the Default Drop Lane icon with your cursor and send an email to the address that appears.

cards.title: Update our logo.
cards.description:
This card is green. That's not because it's feeling squeamish.

That means that it's an "improvement" card. Click the Card Type drop-down menu to see what other types of cards are on this board. 

You can add, change or remove Card Types. Click here to learn more

cards.title: Come up with a schedule for App rollout
cards.description:
We need to schedule this card!

Use the dates right on this card by selecting a Planned Start and Planned Finish date.

cards.title: Build a new Website
cards.description:
You can assign users to a card. 

To do this, click the Assigned Users link on the left navigation menu. 

If you haven't already done so, add a few more users.

cards.title: Q1 Sales Metrics
cards.description:
You can attach documents, graphs, spreadsheets and any other kind of file, by simply dragging and dropping. 

Click the Attachments link on the left navigation menu, to open up the attachments window.

cards.title: Update the company handbook
cards.description:
This is a low-priority task. 

You can visually show the priority of a task on a card by selecting a priority from the drop-down menu on the right. 

Set this card's priority to low, and then save your changes.

cards.title: Learn about the competition
cards.description:
Let's break this work down into more detailed Tasks.

You can add sub-tasks by clicking Tasks in the navigation menu, on the left.

Learn more about Taskboards here.

When you're done, you can drag this card out of the Ready to Start lane, and into In Progress.

cards.title: Cards on this board move from left to right, as work is done
Updating work is just as easy as clicking and dragging. Try it!
Click the '+' or '-' icons at the top of each LeanKit lane to expand or collapse.
cards.description: Open the "Future Work" lane, on the left, now!

cards.title: Write a new Blog post
cards.description:
Ever wonder how to get notified if a card is done?

In LeanKit you can subscribe to either a Card, or to a Lane. 

You can subscribe to a Card by clicking the empty check-box at the bottom of this card's menu. You'll recieve email anytime someone changes anything about this card. 

You can also subscribe to a Lane, by right-clicking on any Lane Header and choosing to subscribe to that lane. You'll recieve an email any time a card move into, out of, or changes inside that lane. 

If you want to get really adventurous, you can even subscribe to a whole Board. You'll get notified anytime someone changes a card anywhere on the board. Do this by clicking the settings icon at the top right-hand corner, and choosing Subscribe from the menu. 

Read more about subscriptions here,

cards.title: Update the Knowledge Base
cards.description:
Add some tags to this card.

Tags can be used to group cards together for any reason. You can even search or filter by tags later. 

Once you use a tag once, you'll see that tag auto-complete from that point on. 

Read more about Tags here:

cards.title: Calendar doesn't look right in IE11
Woah! Red's not good!
cards.description:
Red cards are a great way to show issues on a LeanKit board.

You'll notice this lane is also red. That's because we've violated the support team's WIP (Work In Progress) limit. Read more here.

Help this team out by dragging a card into Ready for Review.

cards.title: Chris is having issues logging in on iPhone
Kelly's phone is frequently dropping calls
Connection is really slow though the company VPN

cards.description:
You've found it! Great job using LeanKit's filter!

Blocked cards have a red stop-sign to indicate there's a problem. 

Now that you've identified it, clicked the Blocked button and (optionally) give a reason to un-block this card.

cards.title: API Improvements
cards.description:
You can leave comments on a card so everyone knows what's going on.

Try leaving a comment on this card for everyone to see. 

Pro Tip: You can @mention users in comments or in this description. Have you added other users yet? You can do that by clicking the "User" icon on the top navigation menu.

cards.title: Let's give our Dev team some more work
cards.description:
You can add cards to a LeanKit board many different ways. 

You can click the "Quick Add" icon, on the top right of any board.

You can right-click any lane to add a new card.

You can even email a card to the board. Have you opened up the "Future Work" lane yet? There's a hint in there :)

cards.title: Find the hidden risk on this board
cards.description:
Agent,

Your mission is to find the risk on this board. Your secret weapon? The LeanKit filter. 

Use the filter to Show Only cards that are Critical Priotity, but are also Blocked.

Learn More about LeanKit's Filter

cards.title: The ? right above me means...
cards.description:
... that this LeanKit lane ( or vertical column ) represents a Connected Card Done Lane. 

You can read more about how LeanKit lets you connect cards across multiple boards in our LeanKit Knowledge Base.

cards.title: For more info on how to get started with LeanKit
cards.description: Visit the Getting Started section of our Knowledge Base

cards.title: For more info on Kanban and Lean
cards.description: Visit the Kanban Learning Center on our website.
